analysis_commentary: The 95th percentile wait time from referral to decision to treat for admitted people has increased in the past 12 months by 0.5 weeks. The 95th percentile wait time from referral to treatment for incomplete pathways has remained around 18.6 weeks for the past 12 months. For non-admitted people the 95th percentile wait time has remained at 16 weeks.
data_source: NHS England, Referral to Treatment waiting times
